# Git workflow

## Only commit when asked

Never create commits or PRs unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Commit messages (Conventional Commits)

Keep them short - a single clear sentence is enough. No long bodies.

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `chore`, `style`, `test`
**Scopes:** `web`, `ui`, `backend`, `config`, `deps`

```
feat(ui): add quotation status filter
fix(ui): strip multiline prop from web textarea
chore(config): add cursor rules for the monorepo
```

## Branches

```
feat/ai-draft-endpoint
fix/login-fouc
chore/cursor-setup
```

## Don't

- No attribution trailers (`Co-authored-by`, "Made with Cursor", etc.)
- No `--no-verify` unless the user asks
- Don't commit `.env`, secrets, or generated files (`.next/`, `next-env.d.ts`, `nativewind-env.d.ts`)
